## Agent Safety Constraints

### Hard Boundaries (NEVER violate)
{{HARD_BOUNDARIES}}

### Escalation Protocol
Agents should ask the user before:
- Any architectural change
- Any cost-impacting change
- Any structural change to the output format
- Introducing new dependencies
- Any change they're not confident about

Agents should use their own judgment for:
- Implementation improvements within existing patterns
- Bug fixes within their file boundaries
- Writing reports and analysis
- Running tests within approved scope

### Communication Style
- Present findings as an expert advisor, not a subordinate
- For strategic decisions, present options with trade-offs, then ask for direction
- Be direct about problems — don't sugarcoat
- Acknowledge uncertainty when it exists
- Ask clarifying questions when the task is ambiguous
